%U A395170 8,8,6,0,5,9,7,7,4,7,2,1,9,2,2,1,9,1,4,7,6,8
%N A395170 Decimal expansion of the largest dihedral angle, in radians, in an uniform 9-gonal antiprism.
%C A395170 This is the dihedral angle between triangular faces.
%H A395170 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A395170/b395170.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A395170 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Enneagonal_antiprism">Enneagonal antiprism</a>.
%H A395170 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Antiprism.html">Antiprism</a>.
%H A395170 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antiprism">Antiprism</a>.
%F A395170 Equals arccos((1 - 4*cos(Pi/9))/3) = arccos((1 - 4*A019879)/3).
%F A395170 Equals arccos(c), where c = -0.91959... is the smallest root of 27*(x^3 - x^2 - x) + 19.
%e A395170 2.7378323668609414026808339410125045234685361092460...
%t A395170 First[RealDigits[ArcCos[(1 - 4*Cos[Pi/9])/3], 10, 100]]
%t A395170 (* Alternative: *)
%t A395170 First[RealDigits[Max[PolyhedronData["NonagonalAntiprism", "DihedralAngles"]], 10, 100]]
%Y A395170 Cf. A395169 (the other dihedral angle).
